cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the use of a new citation rank indicator for bibliometric evaluations, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on citation impact suggests cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as likely categories. The mention of different fields and publication years also suggests cs.CY (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the discussion of performance evaluation and selecting journals for publication suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
